reviewText: I had recently watched Alexa Vega in "From Prada to Nada" and I liked her acting.  She is funny and believable.  She and Luke Arnold did not disappoint me in this story.  They played these rebel teenagers that get in trouble but what comes out of that is beautiful and inspiring music.  Definitely a must see!

reviewText: I really enjoyed this movie, because of the awesome music for one, but also because the main star held onto his dream despite difficult circumstances, including his father not believing in him. It shows what can be done if you keep your focus and don't give up on yourself or your dream. It reminds me in some ways of the movie "August Rush" because the star heard music in everything from tools to nature.
